      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that, but i already had my blood checked last year and they were pretty low. i'm not looking to do it forever, just like a \"loading dose\" for a week to get ahead of the winter slump. i've read that doctors actually prescribe these high doses for people with severe deficiencies. if a doctor would do it, why wouldn't it be okay for me to do it for just a few days? it seems like a logical way to jumpstart my levels.",
